Title: Object: Femme Fellah (Égypte)
Series: L'Orient pittoresque
Series: Les Artistes contemporains
Description: Numbered 160: An Egyptian woman holds an infant over her shoulders, supporting him with her right arm, holding a pot in her left hand; she stands on a grassy terrain, with a shrub at right; beyond at left, a building amid palm trees; published in in 'Les Artistes Contemporains'. 1852 Lithograph on chine collé
Curator's comments: For Curator's Comment see 1880,0710.183. For more information on the series 'Les Artistes contemporains', see 1889, 0608.477.
Bibliographic references: IFF / Inventaire du Fonds Français: Bibliothèque Nationale, Département des Estampes (17)
